Analysis and Insights

Global Amnesia Treatment Market

Amnesia treatment market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022-2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to account to grow at a CAGR of 5.10% in the above mentioned forecast period.

Amnesia is a particularly severe form of memory loss. The Greek word amnesia literally means forgetfulness. Amnesia, on the other hand, is significantly more intricate and severe than ordinary forgetfulness. The memory loss might be transient or permanent, but the term amnesia usually refers to the latter. Head and brain traumas, certain medicines, alcohol, traumatic events, and illnesses like Alzheimer's disease are all possible causes. Signs and symptoms of this condition include forgetfulness, inability to recognize faces and places, confusion, inability to process or store new information, memory loss, and generation of false memories, among others.

The rise in the prevalence of dementia, Alzheimer’s disease, hypothyroidism and brain tumor, will act as major driver that will results in the expansion of market’s growth. Another significant factor influencing the growth rate of amnesia treatment market is the rising healthcare expenditure. Furthermore, advancement in the medical technology, rising initiatives by public and private organisations to spread awareness and growing government funding are the factors that will expand the amnesia treatment market. Other factors such as increase in the demand for effective therapies and rising geriatric population will positively impact the amnesia treatment market’s growth rate. Additionally, high disposable income and changing lifestyle will result in the expansion of amnesia treatment market. Also, growing number of cases of brain injuries, seizures, depression and bipolar disorder will enhance the growth of amnesia treatment market.

Moreover, the rise in the research and development activities and launch of effective therapies will provide beneficial opportunities for the amnesia treatment market in the forecast period of 2022-2029. Also, high unmet need of current treatment and developments in healthcare technology will escalate the growth rate amnesia treatment market in future.

However, high cost associated with the treatment and lack of infrastructure in low-income countries will impede the growth rate of amnesia treatment market. Additionally, complications involved with amnesia will hinder the amnesia treatment market growth. Less awareness will further challenge the market in the forecast period mentioned above.

